Final 
In Stamford Bridge (London)
05-03-58 London XI   (Eng)          2-2 Barcelona (Esp)
          [James Greaves 5, Jim Langley 88pen; Justo Tejada 4, Eulogio Martinez 43]
London XI: Jack Kelsey (Arsenal); Richard Sillett (Chelsea), Ernest Langley (Fulham), 
           Daniel Blanchflower (c), Maurice Norman (both Tottenham Hotspur), 
           Ken Coote (Brentford), Victor Groves (Arsenal), James Greaves (Chelsea), 
           Robert Smith (Tottenham Hotspur), John Haynes (Fulham), George Robb (Bradford)
           Coach: Joseph Mears
Barcelona: Pedro Estrems; Fernando Olivella, Juan Segarra (c), Martin Verges, 
           Enrique Gensana, Enrique Ribelles, Estanislao Basora, 
           Juan de Macedo "Evaristo", Eulogio Martinez, Ramon Villaverde, Justo Tejada
           Coach: Domingo Balmanya
ref: Albert Dusch (Switzerland)
att: 45,466.

In Nuevo Estadio (Barcelona)
01-05-58 Barcelona (Esp)      6-0 London XI (Eng)
          [Luis Suarez 6, 8, Eulogio Martinez 42, Juan de Macedo "Evaristo" 52, 75, 
           Martin Verges 63]
Barcelona:Antonio Ramallets (c); Fernando Olivella, Juan Segarra, Martin Verges, 
          Joaquin Brugue, Enrique Gensana, Justo Tejada, Juan de Macedo "Evaristo", 
          Eulogio Martinez, Luis Suarez, Estanislao Basora
          Coach: Helenio Herrera.
London XI: Jack Kelsey (Arsenal); George Wright (Leyton Orient), Noel Cantwell 
           (West Ham United), Daniel Blanchflower (Tottenham Hotspur) (c), Ken Brown 
           (West Ham United), David Bowen (Arsenal), Terence Medwin (Tottenham Hotspur), 
           Victor Groves (Arseanl), Robert Smith (Tottenham Hotspur), James Bloomfield 
           (Arsenal), James Lewis (Chelsea)
           Coach: Joseph Mears
ref: Albert Dusch (Switzerland)
att: 70,000.
NB: Jack Kelsey was injured after Barcelona"s fourth goal. Victor Groves took his place.

